This paper proposes a new method for tensor factorization, which is a common problem in machine learning applications. The paper focuses on using random projections to reduce the problem to simultaneous matrix diagonalization, which is a numerical method for matrix factorization. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the most relevant sub-category for this topic. Additionally, the paper also mentions knowledge base modeling and parameter estimation in latent variable models, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the spectral information in the tensor, which is related to signal processing and information theory (cs.SI) and numerical analysis (cs.IT). Therefore, the five likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI, and cs.IT, ordered from most to least likely.
